11/10/2009
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The Hague-based International Court of Justice (ICJ) announced on Friday (October 9th) that a total of 30 states and Kosovo will take part in public hearings on the legality of Pristina's independence this December. The procedure was launched by Serbia, who claims Kosovo's unilateral independence violates international law. (Blic - 10/10/09; UN Observer, AP - 09/10/09)
